---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';
import ArtworkSchema from '../../../components/seo/ArtworkSchema.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'Urgencias';
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="Urgencias — Work"
  description="Urgencias (2012). Installation. Museo de Arte Universidad Nacional, Bogota. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>

  <ArtworkSchema
    title="Urgencias"
    year="2012"
    medium="Installation"
    description="Installation at the Museo de Arte Universidad Nacional, Bogota. Related to the hospital investigations of En estado de coma and Extracciones."
    url="https://mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/urgencias/"
  />

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 026</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2012 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Installation &nbsp;/&nbsp; Museo de Arte Universidad Nacional, Bogota</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio: 4/3;">[ Urgencias — Images coming soon ]</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            <em>Urgencias</em> [Emergencies] falls within the line of hospital-based
            investigation that Escallon has developed throughout her career. The hospital
            — as institution, as building, as metaphor for the social body — has been a
            recurring territory in her work since <em>En estado de coma</em> (2005–2007)
            and the <em>Extracciones</em> series.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            Urgency, as a concept, operates across multiple registers: the medical emergency
            that demands immediate intervention, the social urgency of public hospitals in
            crisis, the urgency of architectural heritage deteriorating while no one acts.
            In the emergency room, individual emergency and collective emergency converge —
            the body of the patient and the body of the building, both in critical condition.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The work was presented at the Museo de Arte of the Universidad Nacional in
            Bogota, a space that, owing to its proximity to the Hospital San Juan de Dios
            — where Escallon carried out much of her hospital-based research — establishes
            a geographic and symbolic relationship with the place of origin of this body
            of work.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">RELATED WORKS</h3>
          <ul style="margin-top: var(--s2); list-style: none;">
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              <a href="/maria-elvira-escallon/en/works/en-estado-de-coma/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">En estado de coma (2005–2007)</a>
            </li>
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              <a href="/maria-elvira-escallon/es/obra/extracciones-hospital/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">Extracciones en el Hospital Universitario (2012)</a>
            </li>
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              <a href="/maria-elvira-escallon/es/obra/extraccion/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">Extraccion (2016)</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>Urgencias</strong><br>
            2012<br><br>
            Installation.<br><br>
            Museo de Arte Universidad Nacional, Bogota.<br>
            Variable dimensions.
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">EXHIBITIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Museo de Arte Universidad Nacional — Bogota, 2012
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2012). <em>Urgencias</em>.
            Installation. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/urgencias/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>
